# Plate Pursuit — Project Overview

## What this is

Client-only React SPA for tracking license-plate spotting game progress. No backend, no accounts, no sync.

## Hard constraints

- **Static deploy only** — `npm run build` → `dist/`; no server-side runtime code
- **localStorage only** — key `plate-pursuit:v1`; all progress stays on the user's device
- **Honor system** — user self-reports finds via "Found it!"; do not add plate validation unless explicitly requested
- **One track per variant** — six independent progress streams, not multiple runs of the same variant

## Stack conventions

- React + TypeScript + Vite + React Router
- CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) colocated with components; global resets in `src/index.css`
- State: `ProgressContext` wraps app; pure I/O in `src/storage/progressStore.ts`
- Game logic lives in `src/games/` — UI should not embed sequence rules

## When adding features

- Keep diffs minimal; match existing patterns in surrounding files
- New game variants: add sequence + registry entry + update `VARIANT_IDS` in `types.ts`
- Schema changes: bump `version` in `AppState` and add migration in `progressStore.ts`
